# Path prefixes exempt from the check-typography action.
#
# The original rationale (staying byte-identical to upstream
# whg517/browser-bridge for clean merges) ended with the rebrand to
# chromium-bridge (ADR-0023). This list only holds files that deliberately
# carry non-ASCII text, and it must only ever shrink:
# - src/apps/extension/: the zh locale bundles and the functional glyphs the
#   code emits on purpose - the masking replacement bullets ("****[jwt]"
#   spelled with U+2022, pinned by the masking/egress tests and visible to
#   MCP clients) and their test fixtures. Legitimate CJK here is policed by
#   scripts/check-cjk.ts.
# - src/apps/desktop/ui locales + native-language-names: the desktop app's
#   zh bundles and each language naming itself; same category as above.
# - Translated docs (*.zh_CN.md / *.zh_TW.md): legitimate CJK text and CJK
#   punctuation; each translated file is exempted by exact path so nothing
#   else rides along. English docs are NOT exempt: they are plain ASCII.
# - CHANGELOG.md: generated release history, never edited by hand.
src/apps/extension/
src/apps/desktop/ui/src/locales/
src/apps/desktop/ui/src/lib/native-language-names.ts
README.zh_CN.md
README.zh_TW.md
docs/quickstart.zh_CN.md
docs/quickstart.zh_TW.md
docs/privacy-policy.zh_CN.md
docs/privacy-policy.zh_TW.md
CHANGELOG.md
